dataIdInfo.idAbs: This point data layer represents addresses for Waupaca County, Wisconsin in 2014. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Waupaca_Addresses_2014.gdb. [This feature class represents a comprehensive, spatially referenced collection of rural addresses as recognized by Waupaca County. This layer represents the location/address of primary structures (generally residential housing) throughout the County.]
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer is intended for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [The layer is primarily used as base reference data for digital mapping, emergency response, address centerline geocoding, and consistency checks with other parcel-based information.]
